1.1 Data Source Discovery

I researched and documented data sources for Pet Stores in Berlin, prioritizing open and regularly updated data.

Below are strong starting points (i included them in your README.md):

 1. OpenStreetMap (OSM) Overpass API

. Source and Origin: OpenStreetMap Overpass API

. Update Frequency: Updated continuously (changes propagate within hours)

. Data Type: Dynamic (queryable via API)

. Relevant Fields:

        . name – Store name

        . shop=pet – Tag used for pet stores

        . addr:street, addr:city, addr:postcode – Address details

        . opening_hours – Store hours

        . phone, website, email – Contact info

        . lat, lon – Geocoordinates

. Example Query (for Berlin):       

[out:json][timeout:25];
area["name"="Berlin"]->.searchArea;
(
  node["shop"="pet"](area.searchArea);
  way["shop"="pet"](area.searchArea);
  relation["shop"="pet"](area.searchArea);
);
out center;

 2. Berlin Open Data Portal

. Source and Origin: Berlin Open Data Portal

. Update Frequency: Varies (monthly to annually)

. Data Type: Static/Dynamic (depends on dataset)

. Relevant Fields:

            . Business name

            . Category (pet-related retail)

            . Address, postal code, district

            . Opening hours

            . Website or contact info

. Example dataset to check:

“Gewerbe und Einzelhandel in Berlin” (Businesses and retail trade)

.URL: https://daten.berlin.de/datensaetze

3. Yelp Fusion API

. Source and Origin: Yelp Developers

. Update Frequency: Dynamic (real-time API)

. Data Type: Dynamic (requires API key)

. Relevant Fields:

             . name, location.display_address

             . coordinates.latitude/longitude

             . rating, review_count

             . categories

             . hours

             . url, phone

Query Example:
GET https://api.yelp.com/v3/businesses/search?term=pet+store&location=Berlin

4. Google Places API (optional enrichment)

. Source and Origin: Google Places API

. Update Frequency: Real-time

. Data Type: Dynamic (API, requires key)

. Relevant Fields:

        . Place name

        . Type: “pet_store”

        . Address

        . Opening hours

        . Ratings and reviews

        . Website, phone number

 5. Local Business Directories (Supplemental)

. Examples:

        . Gelbe Seiten Berlin

        . Das Örtliche Berlin

. Update Frequency: Irregular

. Data Type: Static (scraper or manual import)

. Relevant Fields:

              . Business name

              . Address, phone

              . Category/type (e.g., Haustierbedarf, Tierhandlung)
              

